aims-os-desktop (2.1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Slim split for v2.1. The metapackage now keeps only the essentials
    that must be on the live ISO: GNOME + Calamares + Plymouth + one
    browser (Firefox ESR fr) + LibreOffice fr + free codecs + the
    NetworkManager / Flatpak / KeepassXC / shell-tool baseline. Moves
    out:
    + aims-os-desktop-extras  — Chromium, GIMP, Inkscape, Shotwell,
      Evolution, ghostwriter, fish, tilix, flameshot, English
      LibreOffice helpers / dictionaries, non-free codecs.
    + aims-os-desktop-dev     — default-jdk, Gradle, Kotlin, PHP,
      Composer, adb/fastboot, Docker, Podman, kubectl, Ansible, rustup.
  * Adds Breaks: aims-os-desktop (<< 2.1) so the v2.0 -> v2.1 upgrade
    is handled cleanly. Existing v2.0 installs that want the full
    set back: `apt install aims-os-everything` (or pick the extras /
    dev metapackage individually).
  * Drops the explicit Recommends on p7zip-rar — it moves into
    aims-os-desktop-extras alongside the other non-free codecs.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Wed, 27 May 2026 03:00:00 +0000

aims-os-desktop (2.0+3) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Move p7zip-rar from Depends to Recommends. The proprietary RAR
    codec lives in Debian's non-free component, which is enabled by
    the AIMS OS ISO build but not by a vanilla Debian Trixie install.
    Hard Depends on it broke the apt-repo install path on main-only
    setups; Recommends keeps the codec on the ISO and silently skips
    it elsewhere.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Sun, 24 May 2026 14:30:00 +0000

aims-os-desktop (2.0+2) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Modernise the developer toolchain for the 2025-2026 AIMS courses.
    + Containers & orchestration (Web/Android Dev, MLOps): docker.io,
      docker-compose (Trixie's docker-compose 2.26.1 IS Compose v2 —
      the Go binary; Debian kept the legacy package name),
      docker-buildx, podman, kubectl, ansible.
    + Mobile development (Android course): android-tools-adb,
      android-tools-fastboot.
    + Modern dev CLI: neovim, httpie, rustup.
    + Database labs: redis-server (complements redis-tools client).
    + Drop Trixie's nodejs (20.19, EOL April 2026). Node.js 22 LTS
      is installed via NodeSource apt repo in chroot hook 0095.
  * Install via chroot hooks (not in Trixie main):
    + 0095-nodesource — Node.js 22 LTS + bundled npm 10+.
    + 0096-vscodium   — VSCodium (libre VS Code).
    + 0097-cursor     — Cursor AI editor (channel 3.5 pinned).
    + 0098-dbeaver    — DBeaver CE universal SQL GUI.
    + 0099-rust-runtimes — Bun, Deno and uv binaries to /usr/local/bin.
    + 0100-pipx-tools — ruff via system-wide pipx.
    + 0101-user-groups — add live user to docker + wireshark groups.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Sat, 23 May 2026 09:00:00 +0000

aims-os-desktop (2.0+1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Align with the 2025-2026 AIMS curriculum.
    + Web and Android Development course: nodejs, npm, default-jdk
      (Java 21), gradle, kotlin, php-cli, composer. Android Studio
      itself is install-on-demand via Flathub so students get
      current versions.
    + Heritage additions from AIMS Desktop 2020: pandoc (universal
      document converter), pdftk-java (PDF split/merge/rotate), tilix
      (tiling terminal), yt-dlp (offline lecture downloads).
  * Replace neofetch (archived upstream in 2024, removed from Trixie)
    with fastfetch, the actively-maintained C rewrite that produces
    the same screenful of system info.
  * Replace qml-module-qtquick-controls + -controls2 with the Trixie
    Qt6 successor qml6-module-qtquick-controls — Calamares 3.3 in
    Trixie is a Qt6 build and the Qt5 QML modules no longer apply.

 -- AIMS Senegal IT <hakim@aims-senegal.org>  Fri, 22 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

aims-os-desktop (2.0) trixie; urgency=medium

